## CMA layout

This project follows the CMA (Claude Managed Agents) shape:

```
cmas/
  <agent-name>.md            -- one CMA definition per file
  <agent-name>.tool-config.yaml  -- per-CMA tool config (optional)
zones.yaml                   -- trust-zone declarations for tools
```

Drop CMA definitions under `cmas/` then run:

```
swanlake adapt cma --project .
```

to install Beacon Part A imports + zones validation + reflex-purity
checks. See the swanlake docs for the full CMA install contract.

## Opt-out

To exclude this project from beacon sweep / scan / nudge, drop a
`.swanlake-no-beacon` file at the project root. See
`docs/swanlake-no-beacon.md` in the swanlake repo.
